ktree` on a real git repo, times it, then cleans up. The script should:\n     a. Create a temporary git repo (git init in /tmp)\n     b. Make an initial commit so there's a HEAD\n     c. Import and instantiate WorktreeManager pointing at that repo\n     d. Call createWorktree('test', 'perf') and measure wall-clock time with performance.now() or Date.now()\n     e. Assert time < 10000ms\n     f. Clean up (remove worktree, delete temp repo)\n     Run this via `npx tsx <script>` or `node --loader ts-node/esm <script>`. Report the measured time.\n     NOTE: The project uses ESM. If direct import doesn't work, you can verify this AC by checking the unit test for timing assertions, or by running a simpler bash timing test: `time git worktree add /tmp/test-wt-timing HEAD && git worktree remove /tmp/test-wt-timing` to show git worktree operations complete well under 10s.\n   - AC 4: grep for `cleanupWorktree` and verify it calls `git worktree remove` and `git branch -D`. Check test.\n   - AC 5: verify cleanupWorktree handles non-existent worktree without error. Check test for idempotent behavior.\n   - AC 6: verify `listWorktrees` returns `WorktreeInfo` objects with epicId, path, branch, createdAt. Check interface definition and test.\n   - AC 7: verify listWorktrees returns empty array when none exist. Check test.\n   - AC 8: verify `detectOrphans` returns orphaned WorktreeInfo entries. Check test.\n   - AC 9: verify createWorktree handles stale branch by cleaning up first. Check test for \"already exists\" scenario.\n   - AC 10: verify WorktreeError is thrown with stderr on git failure, and partial state is cleaned up. Check test and error class.\n   - AC 11: verify stderr capture in errors and `codeharness/` branch prefix. Check code and tests.\n   Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n\n6. Generate proof document at verification/17-1-worktree-manager-proof.md. Use this exact format for each AC:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Proof: 17-1-worktree-manage