he 10-second NFR1 threshold. The `execGit` method has a 30-second timeout as safety net (line 248).\n38\t```output\n39\tgit worktree add /tmp/codeharness-timing-wt HEAD  0.01s user 0.01s system 55% cpu 0.025 total\n40\tgit worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-timing-wt    0.00s user 0.00s system 82% cpu 0.011 total\n41\t```\n42\t\n43\t## AC 4: cleanupWorktree removes worktree and branch\n44\t\n45\t**Verdict:** PASS\n46\t**Evidence:**\n47\tTest \"removes worktree and branch (AC #4)\" verifies both `git worktree remove --force` and `git branch -D` are called.\n48\t```output\n49\texpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17 --force')) ✓\n50\texpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git branch -D codeharness/epic-17-my-slug')) ✓\n51\t```\n52\t\n53\t## AC 5: cleanupWorktree is idempotent\n54\t\n55\t**Verdict:** PASS\n56\t**Evidence:**\n57\tTest \"is idempotent — no error when nothing exists (AC #5)\" makes all git commands throw, verifies no exception propagates.\n58\t```output\n59\texpect(() => manager.cleanupWorktree('99')).not.toThrow() ✓\n60\t```\n61\t\n62\t## AC 6: listWorktrees returns WorktreeInfo objects\n63\t\n64\t**Verdict:** PASS\n65\t**Evidence:**\n66\tTest \"returns only codeharness-prefixed worktrees (AC #6)\" and \"returns WorktreeInfo with all required fields (AC #6)\" verify epicId, path, branch, and createdAt fields. Interface defined at line 29-38 with all four readonly fields.\n67\t```output\n68\texpect(wt).toHaveProperty('epicId', '5') ✓\n69\texpect(wt).toHaveProperty('path', '/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-5') ✓\n70\texpect(wt).toHaveProperty('branch', 'codeharness/epic-5-slug') ✓\n71\texpect(wt).toHaveProperty('createdAt') ✓\n72\t```\n73\t\n74\t## AC 7: listWorktrees returns empty array when none exist\n75\t\n76\t**Verdict:** PASS\n77\t**Evidence:**\n78\tTest \"returns empty array when no codeharness worktrees exist (AC #7)\" parses porcelain output with only the main worktree, returns empty array.\n79\t```output\n80\texpect(result).toEqual([]) ✓\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\t## AC 8: detectOrphans returns orphaned entries\n84\t\n85\t**Verdict:** PASS\n86\t**Evidence:**\n87\tThree tests cover orphan detection: no lane-state.json, no PID in lane-state.json, dead PID. Plus a test for non-orphaned (live PID) returning empty. And corrupt lane-state.json edge case.\n88\t```output\n89\t\"identifies worktrees without lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n90\t\"identifies worktrees with no PID in lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n91\t\"identifies worktrees with dead PID as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n92\t\"does NOT mark worktree as orphaned if PID is alive (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 0 ✓\n93\t\"treats corrupt lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n94\t```\n95\t\n96\t## AC 9: createWorktree handles stale branch\n97\t\n98\t**Verdict:** PASS\n99\t**Evidence:**\n100\tTests \"cleans up stale branch before re-creating (AC #9)\" and \"cleans up stale worktree directory before re-creating (AC #9)\" verify cleanup of both stale branches and worktree directories before re-creation.\n101\t```output\n102\texpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git branch -D codeharness/epic-17-old-slug')) ✓\n103\texpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17 --force')) ✓\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t## AC 10: WorktreeError thrown with stderr, partial state cleaned up\n107\t\n108\t**Verdict:** PASS\n109\t**Evidence:**\n110\tTest \"throws WorktreeError with stderr on git failure (AC #10)\" verifies WorktreeError with stderr. Test \"cleans up partial state on failure — branch created but worktree fails (AC #10)\" verifies `git branch -D` cleanup after partial creation.\n111\t```output\n112\texpect(err).toBeInstanceOf(WorktreeError) ✓\n113\texpect((err as WorktreeError).stderr).toContain('fatal: not a git repository') ✓\n114\texpect(call