ecGit(\\`git worktree add ${worktreePath} ${branchName}\\`)`.\n```output\nexpect(path).toBe('/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17') ✓\nexpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git worktree add /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17 codeharness/epic-17-worktree-manager')) ✓\n```\n\n## AC 3: createWorktree completes in under 10 seconds (runtime-provable)\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nRuntime timing test on a real git repo: `git worktree add` completed in 0.025s (25ms), `git worktree remove` in 0.011s. Both well under the 10-second NFR1 threshold. The `execGit` method has a 30-second timeout as safety net (line 248).\n```output\ngit worktree add /tmp/codeharness-timing-wt HEAD  0.01s user 0.01s system 55% cpu 0.025 total\ngit worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-timing-wt    0.00s user 0.00s system 82% cpu 0.011 total\n```\n\n## AC 4: cleanupWorktree removes worktree and branch\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTest \"removes worktree and branch (AC #4)\" verifies both `git worktree remove --force` and `git branch -D` are called.\n```output\nexpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17 --force')) ✓\nexpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git branch -D codeharness/epic-17-my-slug')) ✓\n```\n\n## AC 5: cleanupWorktree is idempotent\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTest \"is idempotent — no error when nothing exists (AC #5)\" makes all git commands throw, verifies no exception propagates.\n```output\nexpect(() => manager.cleanupWorktree('99')).not.toThrow() ✓\n```\n\n## AC 6: listWorktrees returns WorktreeInfo objects\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTest \"returns only codeharness-prefixed worktrees (AC #6)\" and \"returns WorktreeInfo with all required fields (AC #6)\" verify epicId, path, branch, and createdAt fields. Interface defined at line 29-38 with all four readonly fields.\n```output\nexpect(wt).toHaveProperty('epicId', '5') ✓\nexpect(wt).toHaveProperty('path', '/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-5') ✓\nexpect(wt).toHaveProperty('branch', 'codeharness/epic-5-slug') ✓\nexpect(wt).toHaveProperty('createdAt') ✓\n```\n\n## AC 7: listWorktrees returns empty array when none exist\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTest \"returns empty array when no codeharness worktrees exist (AC #7)\" parses porcelain output with only the main worktree, returns empty array.\n```output\nexpect(result).toEqual([]) ✓\n```\n\n## AC 8: detectOrphans returns orphaned entries\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nThree tests cover orphan detection: no lane-state.json, no PID in lane-state.json, dead PID. Plus a test for non-orphaned (live PID) returning empty. And corrupt lane-state.json edge case.\n```output\n\"identifies worktrees without lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n\"identifies worktrees with no PID in lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n\"identifies worktrees with dead PID as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n\"does NOT mark worktree as orphaned if PID is alive (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 0 ✓\n\"treats corrupt lane-state.json as orphaned (AC #8)\" — orphans.length === 1 ✓\n```\n\n## AC 9: createWorktree handles stale branch\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTests \"cleans up stale branch before re-creating (AC #9)\" and \"cleans up stale worktree directory before re-creating (AC #9)\" verify cleanup of both stale branches and worktree directories before re-creation.\n```output\nexpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git branch -D codeharness/epic-17-old-slug')) ✓\nexpect(calls).toContainEqual(expect.stringContaining('git worktree remove /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-17 --force')) ✓\n```\n\n## AC 10: WorktreeError thrown with stderr, partial state cleaned up\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n**Evidence:**\nTest \"throws WorktreeError with stderr on git failure (AC #10)\" verifies WorktreeError with stderr. Test \"cleans up partial state on failure — branch created but worktree fails (AC #10)\" verifies